Package: nlmixr2libingest
Title: Token-Efficient Ingestion Tooling for the 'nlmixr2lib' Model Library
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("William", "Denney", email = "wdenney@humanpredictions.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Corpus-scale tooling that makes extracting published
    population pharmacokinetic / pharmacodynamic models into 'nlmixr2lib'
    cheaper and more reliable. Provides deterministic filtering of R check
    and vignette-render logs, a fast lookup over the 'nlmixr2lib' canonical
    name registers (covariate, compartment, and parameter), and -- in later
    phases -- structural model features, archetype templates, a fittable
    classifier, and local-LLM-assisted distillation. The package consumes
    'nlmixr2lib' (its registers, compiled model database, and authoring API)
    but never reimplements its model validation, which remains in
    'nlmixr2lib'. Optional local-LLM features degrade gracefully so the
    package runs with no LLM configured.
